# Incident Escalation Matrix

## Escalation Criteria

### When to Escalate
- Incident remains unresolved beyond SLA timeframe
- Issue complexity exceeds current team capabilities
- Multiple systems affected
- Senior stakeholder involvement required
- Potential for significant business impact

## Escalation Levels

### Level 1: Service Desk / First Line Support
- **Response Time**: 15 minutes (P1), 1 hour (P2)
- **Scope**: Initial triage, basic troubleshooting
- **Contact**: servicedesk@company.com

### Level 2: Technical Support Team
- **Response Time**: 30 minutes (P1), 2 hours (P2)
- **Scope**: Advanced troubleshooting, system investigation
- **Contact**: techsupport@company.com

### Level 3: Senior Engineers / Specialists
- **Response Time**: 45 minutes (P1), 4 hours (P2)
- **Scope**: Complex technical issues, architecture changes
- **Contact**: [Contact details]

### Level 4: Management / Executive
- **Response Time**: 1 hour (P1)
- **Scope**: Business-critical decisions, major outages
- **Contact**: [Contact details]

